race.comment: FAME CHASER (9) wasn't far away on debut last start over 1106m at Ellis Park (Turf), finishing third and beaten 3 lengths. Likely improver who is expected to be in the finish. STATE CONCEAL (11) finished fourth two runs back then improved last start but found one better over 1207m at Colonial Downs, beaten only 1.5 lengths after being prominent at the corner. Has his share of talent. Hard to beat in this suitable race. ZUCCHERO (1) was safely held on debut last start, finishing 20 lengths behind the winner in tenth over 1408m at Kentucky (Turf). Drew wide on that occasion but has the inside gate this time. Will take a lot from that experience. One of the main contenders. PERFECT AUDIBLE (8) was in contention on the bend and finished second last start over 1308m at Churchill Downs (Dirt), beaten 5.5 lengths. Should take a lot from that hit-out. Capable of another bold effort.
